Spec cheat-sheet (full schema: `src/deckstudio/spec/schema.py`; worked
example: `decks/_example-quarterly/spec.yaml`).

Slide types: title, section, agenda, content, big_number, comparison,
timeline, icon_row, quote, table, chart, thanks.

Hard rules:
- Every slide: unique kebab-case `id` (stable вЂ” feedback references it),
  `type`, and for most types an assertion `title` (в‰¤90 chars).
- No colors, fonts, or positions вЂ” only semantic hints:
  `emphasize`, `sentiment`, `highlight`, `animate: none|fade|build`
  (animations require deck-level `animations: subtle` вЂ” desktop-PowerPoint
  presentations only; previews/phones mis-render them).
- `variant:` picks a layout composition per slide (see the catalog's
  variant table). Usually omit it вЂ” defaults vary by deck automatically.
- Inline markup in text: `**bold**`, `[accent]text[/accent]`. Nothing else.
- Limits that encode design (don't fight them, redesign the slide):
  agenda в‰¤6, bullets в‰¤6 (в‰¤160 chars each), stats 1-4, comparison bullets в‰¤5,
  milestones 2-6, icon_row items 2-4, table в‰¤6 cols Г— в‰¤8 rows, pie/doughnut
  в‰¤6 slices, chart series в‰¤6.
- `stats`: `arrow` is the visual direction, `sentiment` the color вЂ”
  a falling lapse rate is `arrow: down, sentiment: good`.
- Every chart needs `insight:` (its "so what") and matching series lengths;
  `highlight: {series, point}` accents the data point that carries the story.
- Speaker notes (`notes:`) carry the detail; slides carry the message.
- Deck level: always fill `audience` and `intent`.

After editing: `deckstudio validate <deck>` then `deckstudio build <deck>`.
Design suggestions from validate encode the playbooks вЂ” act on them or have a
reason not to.
